/-!
# Small-divisor series bound

This file proves the bound
`‚ąĎ_{d ‚Č§ s, d ‚ą£ q, d > 1} ‚ąŹ_{p ‚ą£ d} k ¬∑ p^{‚ąíőĶ} ‚Č§ K ¬∑ s^{1 ‚ąí őĶ/2}`
for squarefree `q`, using the **elementary factorization path**:

1. For primes `p ‚Č• k^{2/őĶ}`, we have `k ¬∑ p^{‚ąíőĶ/2} ‚Č§ 1`.
2. The multiplicative function `f(d) = ‚ąŹ_{p‚ą£d} (k ¬∑ p^{‚ąíőĶ/2})` is bounded
   by a constant `M(k,őĶ)` (the product over the finitely many primes
   `p < k^{2/őĶ}`).
3. This gives `‚ąŹ_{p‚ą£d} k ¬∑ p^{‚ąíőĶ} ‚Č§ M ¬∑ d^{‚ąíőĶ/2}` for squarefree `d`.
4. Summing `d^{‚ąíőĶ/2}` up to `s` and comparing to `‚ąę‚āĀňĘ x^{‚ąíőĶ/2} dx`
   yields `O(s^{1‚ąíőĶ/2})`.
